===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# Any of very many [[animal]]s (either hermaphroditic or nonhermaphroditic), of the class [[Gastropoda]], having a coiled [[shell]].
#* {{quote-book|year=1963|author={{w|Margery Allingham}}|title={{w|The China Governess}}
|chapter=7|url=http://openlibrary.org/works/OL2004261W
|passage=‘Children crawled over each other like little grey worms in the gutters,’ he said. ‘The only red things about them were their buttocks and they were raw. Their faces looked as if '''snails''' had slimed on them and their mothers were like great sick beasts whose byres had never been cleared. […]’}}
# {{lb|en|informal|by extension}} A slow person; a [[sluggard]].
# {{lb|en|engineering}} A [[spiral]] [[cam]], or a flat piece of metal of spirally curved outline, used for giving motion to, or changing the position of, another part, as the hammer tail of a striking clock.
# {{lb|en|military|historical}} A [[tortoise]] or [[testudo]]; a movable roof or shed to protect besiegers.
#* Vegetius (in translation)
#*: They had also all manner of gynes [engines] {{...}} that needful is [in] taking or sieging of castle or of city, as '''snails''', that was naught else but hollow pavises and targets, under the which men, when they fought, were heled [protected] {{...}}
# The [[pod]] of the {{vern|snail clover}}.

